25 February 2022 Following the delivery of the 2022 State of the Nation Address (SoNA), the Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) will, on Sunday 27 February 2022, host a media briefing of the Justice, Crime Prevention and Security Cluster led by the Minister of Defence and Military Veterans, Ms Thandi Modise and the Minister of Police, Gen Bheki Cele. The briefing will amplify areas of the work of the Cluster and departments in the Cluster, which President Ramaphosa addressed in the State of the Nation Address. Members of the media are invited to cover the briefing as follows: Date: Sunday, 27 February 2022Time: 11:00Venue: Ronnie Mamoepa Press Room, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Francis Baard Street, Hatfield, Pretoria. NB: Live streaming details will be confirmed at a later stage. RSVP: Ignicious Masilela on ignicious@gcis.gov.za(link sends e-mail) Enquiries:Siphiwe DlaminiCell: 083 645 4294